<subSubSection id="C3276FE1FFF5F5240CE9DCD1FEE3FEC4" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9DCD1FDBEFF19" blockId="24.[168,512,159,184]" box="[168,512,159,184]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<heading id="D0CA8B06FFF5F5240CE9DCD1FDBEFF19" box="[168,512,159,184]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DCD1FDBEFF19" bold="true" box="[168,512,159,184]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D47E9FFF5F5240CE9DCD1FED8FF16" box="[168,358,159,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eragrostis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DCD1FED8FF16" bold="true" box="[168,358,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Eragrostis pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) P.Beauv.
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9DCB6FEE3FEC4" blockId="24.[168,779,199,748]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DCB6FEF4FF7E" bold="true" box="[168,330,199,223]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Identification.</emphasis>
Annual tussock grass, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240E0ADCB6FD06FF7F" box="[587,696,199,223]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.95" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="69.5" valueMax="85.0" valueMin="54.0">54–85 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades lanceolate, glabrous, without glandules, 4.5– 23.0 cm long, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240D08DD7BFE7CFE80" box="[329,450,266,290]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.5 cm</quantity>
wide, ligulate. Characterized by its open panicle, 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240D3EDD5DFE62FEE2" box="[383,476,300,324]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="16.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="8.0">8–24 cm</quantity>
long, 2.– 
<quantity id="4CC5918FFFF5F5240E00DD5AFD2CFEE2" box="[577,658,299,323]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8 cm</quantity>
wide, with hairs on the axil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3276FE1FFF5F5240CE9DD05FD08FE2D" box="[168,694,372,396]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9DD05FD08FE2D" blockId="24.[168,779,199,748]" box="[168,694,372,396]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DD05FEE3FE2D" bold="true" box="[168,349,372,396]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Common name.</emphasis>
Capim-peludo; Capim-orvalho.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3276FE1FFF5F5240CE9DDEAFF40FD9F" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9DDEAFD8EFE75" blockId="24.[168,779,199,748]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DDEAFEA9FE12" bold="true" box="[168,279,411,435]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Remarks.</emphasis>
Species uncommon on the native grassland, occurring mainly on disturbed sites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B823C6AFFF5F5240CE9DD92FF40FD9F" blockId="24.[168,779,199,748]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis id="B949E078FFF5F5240CE9DD92FED3FE5A" bold="true" box="[168,365,483,507]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest, North (AP, PA and RR states), Northeast (except SE state), South, and Southeast regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
